events.name: Golden State Warriors at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 20 of his 40 points in the fourth quarter, hitting three straight 3-pointers, and the NBA-leading Golden State Warriors overcame a 13-point deficit to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 104-89 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry scores 20 of 40 points in 4th, Warriors beat Cavs
Butler has 32 points, Heat beat Wizards to open 2-game set

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 17 of his 28-points in a third-quarter rally in the Memphis Grizzlies’ 120-108 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant has big 3rd quarter, Grizzlies beat Clippers 120-108

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 25 points and 12 rebounds to help the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the San Antonio Spurs 115-90 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Russell lead Wolves past Spurs 115-90

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored 22 points, Seth Curry added 20 and the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers beat the Denver Nuggets 103-89 on Thursday night to snap a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey, 76ers beat Nuggets 103-89 to snap 5-game skid

headlines.description: — Rudy Gay showed he still knows how to make a major impact on a game even while playing limited minutes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rudy Gay scores 20 points in season debut, Jazz beat Raptors
